Stanford Bunny — time-series export (ExportBunny_0.vtp through ExportBunny_63.vtp)

All files in this directory are derived from the Stanford Bunny model from
the Stanford 3D Scanning Repository.

Source: Stanford 3D Scanning Repository
URL: http://graphics.stanford.edu/data/3Dscanrep/

Reference:
    Turk, G. and Levoy, M. "Zippered Polygon Meshes from Range Images."
    Proceedings of SIGGRAPH '94, ACM, pp. 311-318, 1994.

Stanford's conditions of use:
    You are welcome to use the data and models for research purposes. You
    are also welcome to mirror or redistribute them for free. Such models
    or images are not to be used for commercial purposes, nor should they
    appear in a product for sale (with the exception of scholarly journals
    or books), without permission from the Stanford Computer Graphics
    Laboratory.

    The bunny is explicitly exempted from Stanford's cultural-sensitivity
    restrictions: "You can do anything you want to the Stanford bunny or
    the armadillo."

Required acknowledgement: credit the Stanford Computer Graphics Laboratory.

